http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Gopakumar-to-be-remembered/article13992876.ece

The Kerala chapter of the Indian Veterinary Association will be observing the first death anniversary of C. Gopakumar, veterinary officer who was killed by a captive elephant in musth at Vaipur, near Mallappally, a year ago, in Thiruvalla on Monday.Mathew T. Thomas, MLA, will inaugurate the programme. P.S. Easa, Wildlife Board of India member and former director of the Kerala Forest Research Institute in Peechi, will lead a scientific session on ‘Elephants- In wild and captivity.’— Special Correspondent